-- India cbank chief: need to look at governance of state-run banks 
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Tue Aug 05, 2014 02:23AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 5 (Reuters) - India needs to look again at the governance of state-run banks, central bank chief Raghuram Rajan said on Tuesday, commenting days after the head of Syndicate Bank Ltd <SBNK.NS> was arrested over allegations that he was seeking bribes to favour debtors.

